                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18440408-1295-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1295-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1295-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp> for stealing 1 kettle, value 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and 1 copper, value 14<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18440408-name-1436" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1436" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1436" type="surname" value="GARDNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1436" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440408-1295-offence-1 t18440408-name-1436"></join>William Gardner</persName>, and fixed to a certain building.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1437" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1437" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1437" type="surname" value="GARDNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1437" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM GARDNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a broker, and live in Rose and Crown-court, Moorfields. On Sunday the 7th of April, between three and four o'clock, I saw my copper fixed in my washhouse—my copper tea-kettle was there safe—next morning I found the copper had been pulled down and taken away, and the kettle was missing—these are them—(<hi rend="italic">produced.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1438" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1438" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1438" type="surname" value="TILLIER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1438" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM TILLIER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 28.) On Monday morning at half-past six o'clock, I was on duty in Old-street, St. Luke's, and saw the prisoner carrying a kettle—another lad was with him carrying a copper. I asked the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184404080219"></xptr>
               <p>prisoner where he was going—he Said to No. 9, Goswell-street—I said that will not do—I took him to Bunhill-row—the prisoner threw down the copper, and the other the kettle—I pursued and took the prisoner, but the other escaped.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was not what the prisoner said that he was going to Goswell-street? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I asked him where—he said, No. 9—I swear I said that before the Magistrate—this is my writing—(<hi rend="italic">looking at his deposition</hi>)—it is not here—he said the other met him and asked him to carry it for him into <hi rend="italic">Gosling-street</hi>, and he would give him 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he afterwards said he met him in the Haymarket, Whitechapel.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">called</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1439" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1439" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1439" type="surname" value="PECK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1439" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY PECK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am employed in a wholesale Berlin warehouse in Cheap<lb></lb>side, and carry on business for myself at Kingsland—the prisoner was in my employ, up to the time he was taken into custody, eighteen months altogether—I had given him a holiday on Easter Monday—to the best of my belief Old-street is a quarter of a mile from where the copper was taken from—he was on his way to me to ask for another day's holiday.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1440" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1440" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1440" type="surname" value="TILLIER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1440" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM TILLIER</persName>
                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I knew the other lad to be associated with thieves—he has kept out of the way—I know the prisoner by sight—I know no wrong of him.</p>
